description:
Jonas and Alan Anderson return to the Dream World, only to find themselves caught in an ageless battle between the rag-tag, mercenary Dream Walkers and the mysterious, evil REM, whose plans to take over the Waking World set his focus on young Jonas. Created by Tom DeLonge, founder and frontman of the bands Blink-182 and Angels and Airwaves, this fantastic adventure traces the origin of the mysterious guardian Dream Walker known only in whispered circles as "Poet."

Note: The digital edition (6/10/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Reindeer Games

Get ready for the pulse-pounding origin of Skater X! Who is Javi Buccanero? What's his connection to Theo and the mysterious power of the Radical Guardian? And who won the competition at the skate park last Christmas? All those answers and more are in this issue - along with the shocking surprise guest stars you have to see to believe! Are you ready for REINDEER GAMES?
name: Reindeer Games

description:
The Tale of Little John

As John contemplates his future as an outlaw, Rob's exploits take a darker turn as he grapples with stealing more than medicine.
name: The Tale of Little John

volume.name: Robin Hood: Outlaw of the 21st Century

description:
Disgraced inquisitor Conrad of Marburg has been forced to abandon his erstwhile ward Elisabeth and the young monk, Clement, while he races to Prague with what he believes is the solution to the ultimate enigma of the Third Testament. However, he is captured by the brutal Sayn and must do everything he can to escape! But Elisabeth and Clement have realized the solution Conrad has is wrong… can they catch up with him before all is lost and the incredible knowledge he has uncovered falls to the forces of darkness? Find out in this the stunning final installment of The Third Testament.

Note: The digital edition (6/10/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Book 4: The Day of The Raven

description:
QSTS-329

The stress of a double life is starting to show on Selene. Time's running out for her as the Torchbearer's latest mission threatens to reveal Selene's true intentions: to both the Torchbearers and Prometheus Inc.
name: QSTS-329

description: "The Enemy". In issue 3 of the 'Valley of Death' mini series, 'Journal' becomes fascinated with the story of a prisoner of war who belonged to a small tribe that has lived in the A Shau Valley for centuries. They have no sense of country, politics or idealogy, only for their local people, but they are dragged anyhow into a war they couldn’t even comprehend. Part 3 of 4.
name: The Enemy

description:
Bury My Parts At Squeaky Knee

A terrible storm continues brewing' for Obadiah Dirt and his strange friend, The Stranger. Pony herds, fistfights, and the obligatory dead Marshal are all in this exciting Wee Western!
name: Bury My Parts At Squeaky Knee

description:
WARRIOR AND DEFENDER

Yi Soon Shin versus Wakizaka Yasuharu. What happens when two undefeated commanders meet face-to-face on the battlefield? Absolute carnage! Witness one of the greatest naval battles ever fought in world history as it is re-imagined in this double-sized explosive conclusion to the first epic arc of the YI SOON SHIN Trilogy.
name: Warrior and Defender

description: He's faced them all, but Ashley J. Williams is about to face the greatest horror of his entire deadite-kickin' career - a comic book convention! But this ain't any ol' comic book convention, this one features a special appearance from the president of the United States of America - Barack Obama! How do things go from there when Ash and Obama are in the same place at the same time? And did we happen to mention that the Necronomicon is there doing the thing it does best - turning ordinary humans into the demon possessed undead! This special Army of Darkness mini-series event is written by Elliott (Army of Darkness/Xena) Serrano, illustrated by Ariel Padilla and features covers by Todd (Amazing Spider-Man) Nauck and Lucio (RED SONJA) Parillo! Collected here for the very first time!
name: TPB

volume.name: Army of Darkness: Ash Saves Obama

description:
The next thrilling chapter in the life of "Chosen One" Ashley J. Williams beings here! Opening with a return to the past, Ash has reluctantly embraced his role of humanity's protector and fully taken on the job of guarding the world against the evil powers of the Necronomicon. What could go wrong? Well, just about everything...

Featuring issues 13-17 of DYNAMITE ENTERTAINMENT's fan favorite comic books series, HELLBILLIES and DEADNECKS features the writing team of James Kuhoric and Mike Raicht, along with artist Scott Cohn! Also included in this trade paperback collection is a complete cover gallery, featuring the art of Stjepan (The Darkness, Witchblade) Sejic and Fabiano (ARMY OF DARKNESS/MARVEL ZOMBIES) Neves!
name: Volume 9

volume.name: Army of Darkness: Hellbillies and Deadnecks

description: Atop a hill on the outskirts of town lies an adorable castle that has been the inspiration behind Caroline O'Donald's fairy-tale fantasies ever since she was a little girl. Now as an adult, she's put herself up for auction and, lo and behold, her beloved castle's prince is the winning bidder! Assuming the castle will be more magnificent in real life than it is in her dreams, she steps inside only to find that it's run-down and in need of a lot of love... much like its prince, the handsome recluse Gideon Tremayne!
name: Vol. 1

description: Writer Brandon (NBSG: Zarek) Jerwa is joined series artist Jackson Herbert for this all new series which tells the untold tale of the crew of the Battlestar Galactica! Set approximately two years before the SCI FI mini-series which relaunched Battlestar Galactica to such acclaim, the 7-issues collected here (including #0) follows Commander Adama and crew as they take on their first mission on board the Galactica. Everything in that time frame is explored, including the menace and return of the Cylons as events hurtle towards the Apocalypse! Also includes a complete cover gallery!
name: Volume 1

description: Betty and Veronica are getting married?! Well, no, not yet -- but they sure are thinking about it! Join the girls in this digital-only collection as they attend, plan and daydream about the special day when they marry that special someone. Will that person be Archie, though? Or someone else..?
A magazine sized anthology of horror comics about demonology & exorcism. CANAAN CULT REVIVAL is an explicit and graphic compilation of horror, designed to distress its readers.

The Case of the Undying Detective

Rabbit Black - a freelancer who makes a living solving other people's problems - unexpectedly finds himself murdered but not dead. This unusual state is likely thanks to two facts:

1. magic, like heat, rises and

2. the necromancer in the unit below is terrible at wards.

Tied to said necromancer by the same magic that's keeping him alive(ish,) Rabbit has no choice but to drag Ira Smith around with him as he solves his final problem: who killed Rabbit Black?
name: The Case of the Undying Detective

description:
A corrupt undertaker facing a more-than-divine judgment. A fiddle made of flesh and bone that can only play the song of its creation. A man wakes up to find his doppelganger smiling at him. Mysterious old men who peer into the second-floor windows of sleeping children.

These and other mysterious events haunt the world of The Cousin of Death and Other Unexplainable Events, a book that finds horror in the folk tales of the deep past and in the all-too-immediate, chillingly possible present.

volume.name: The Cousin of Death and Other Unexplainable Events

description: El Cabron Pistolero, a lone gunslinger who's only purpose is to send the demons roaming this earth back to hell.

Long Time No See

Ray and Rita want to have a child: the time is right. Suddenly the past comes knocking at their door: Ray's childhood friend has just been released from prison and pays him an untimely visit, and things start to burn.
name: Long Time No See

description:
Bullets and Blades

An anthology of 3 different stories from revenge (No One) to cyborg zombies (RuinNation) to a deadly samurai (Sins of a Warlord.)
name: Bullets and Blades

description: The final installment of the Jungle Book trilogy has arrived! As each tribe makes a power play to become stronger in the war between species, a human girl stands at the center of it all. Mowglii is the one person who may be able to end the war and bring the species together and fight against a much greater threat. The epic, action-packed hit series returns this Summer!
name: Volume Three

volume.name: Grimm Fairy Tales presents The Jungle Book: Fall of the Wild

description: Two Friends take a weekend retreat at an old cabin, hoping or relaxation and catching up over beers. But their reunion is cut short by an onslaught of terror. What happens next is a surprise to everyone involved.

Level One: Tutorial Level

A young couple discover a strange app on their phone
name: Level One: Tutorial Level

description:
The Day They Arrived, Part 1

A young teen boy in the rural mid-west is the sole witness to the arrival of an alien ship. Who are they? Why are they here? And what will their arrival mean for the future of humanity?
name: The Day They Arrived, Part 1

volume.name: Keith C Bradbury's The Peregrin Chronicles

description: On August 12, 2000, the Russian Submarine Kursk was lost with all hands on board. Witness the definitive version of Sasha Janowicz' rendition of this chilling tale in graphic novel format.

Deepak Chopra presents the tales of the immortal gods and goddesses of Indian myth who reign over humanity and wield the forces of the Universe. The tale of Andhaka, the Blind One. Born deformed, blind, and marooned at the door of the demon kingdom. Brought up under the harsh regimen of the demon warriors, Andhaka learnt to overcome and even surpass his natural disabilities, rising rapidly in the ranks of the demons. Ultimately, as their King, he embarks on a brutal campaign that brings him to the doorsteps of Mount Kailash, the abode of Lord Shiva and Uma. Here, a sad and awful truth awaits the blind champion of the demons, the truth behind his birth and his karma.

Deepak Chopra presents the tales of the immortal gods and goddesses of Indian myth who reign over humanity and wield the forces of the Universe. A never before seen story adaptation on one of the mightiest heroes of the Indian pantheon, the Avian warrior Garuda. Born with blazing gilded wings of a hawk and the body of a man, Garuda became the sworn enemy of his half-brothers, the slithering serpents. When the crafty snakes hold his mother hostage and demand that Garuda steal the nectar of Immortality from the gods, the warrior Garuda is caught between his own oath of walking the path of dharma and saving his mother.

What constitutes a "good" city?

Do city planners really have control over the success of the cities they design?

Ben is a young architect who suddenly appears in a dangerous, apocalyptic world. He knows what he's doing there - He's on a mission to investigate the city. The only person he gravitates towards and communicates with is a violent, rebellious anarchist. It soon becomes apparent that they both share knowledge about the city: They both know that it changes. The city's plan, its buildings, roads, streets - everything changes, disappears and reappears elsewhere - suddenly and without warning.

Surprisingly, no other person is aware of the changes to the city but the two of them. Together they embark on a journey in which a new, futuristic world unfolds before them, while attempting to learn the reason behind the city's transformations. Their journey will change the way they view the world.

Worst Birthday Ever

Meet The Clinton House Boys, who 30 years ago possessed the world's first superpowers.

Now it's happening again and it's up to them to assist, train, or defeat the next generation of superhumans.
name: Worst Birthday Ever

description: Is there life after death? People across the globe have been trying to answer this question since the beginning of time. Many have had near death experiences claiming to have seen the light. Some have claimed to arrive at heavens gates. Some claim to have spoken to dead souls below. But no one has ever been able to prove it... until now. Rogue scientist, Professor Alscott, secretly hired by the Vatican, sets out to prove what no one else has. Does heaven and hell really exist? With the help of his four brightest students, Professor Alscott sets out to prove this age old question by putting his students in near death conditions and recording what they see. It works! Until something goes terribly wrong... Created by Liquid Comics and producer Eric Eisner's, "Epic Cycle" graphic novel imprint. Written by Julian Metter with artwork by Edison George (John Woo's Seven Brothers, Beyond).
name: Vol. 1

description:
The city of Salemscraft Wells was stalked by a serial killer years ago. When the case seemed forgotten, our intrepid and sexy journalist Sidney is called by a group of eccentric rockstars to resume the investigation... and to smash some zombie heads! An old-school mystery filled to the brim with pulp action, gore-ish comedy and curves!

Note: The digital edition (6/10/2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

This is my first full length comic book outside of many years of making zines, under the title Some Scraps.

This collection was created over two years. Mostly semi-surreal stories with bizarre characters, and a few autobiographical comics.
name: Vol. 1

description:
SQUIRREL #1: HIT-N-RUN

Squirrel uncovers one of Mr. Q's weapons smuggling rings and must take on the muscle bound enforcer "8-Ball" alone!

Also featuring a bonus Cy-Boar story by Doug Curtis!

CY-BOAR #2.5: THE DEAD

Plagued by strange dreams of his dead friends, Cy-Boar must unravel a mystery involving toxic gas and zombies!
name: Hit-n-Run; The Dead

description:
Independently published and critically acclaimed, "SUPER!" follows a ragtag team of amateur heroes as they struggle to make a name for themselves in a universe dominated by more popular, established teams. In the grand tradition of "the Venture Bros." and "Mystery Men", "SUPER!" is a loving homage to the genre that knows when to laugh at itself and isn't afraid to poke fun at comic tropes along the way. Amidst the craziness and chaos of a new comic universe where supers are commonplace, the greatest superhero story of our generation is about to begin...

"SUPER!" Volume One is a stunning, full-color compilation of the first five issues of this ground-breaking comic by Unlikely Heroes Studios, lauded by critics everywhere as "...the kind of comic you want to be reading." So come along with Blitz, the Furious Fire-Ant, Max Archer, and the rest of the team as they square off against the forces of evil and their own hilarious shortcomings. Don't miss your chance to own this handheld, action-packed thrillride!
name: Volume One

description:
Chapter One - Eyes

A seemingly ordinary bank clerk’s life takes a turn for the bizarre: Laurence is being hunted by something that may exist beyond the boundaries of the natural. What are they, what do they want? And why can’t he remember a thing from the past so recent..?
name: Chapter One: Eyes

description: In his caricatures and illustrations, Nikolic discovers the truth about our contemporary society. He is a cool assessor of the situation and committed resistance fighter, but never crosses the line of lasciviousness, does not call the names of individuals, and shows problems predominantly as metaphysical ideas.
